Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Zommunity is an early stage technology startup founded in the heart of Silicon Beach in Santa Monica, California. Zommunity is the Zero hassle, Zero ad, Zero cost website for community-based classified advertising and sharing of information. Unlike "that list" and other existing classified advertising websites which merely focus on general ads for general audience, the audience for an ad in Zommunity is solely a community, i.e., a special category of people with common ideas or needs.  Example communities include but are not limited to any faith, ethnicity, college, etc. For example someone in the Jewish community might be looking for a nanny who observes Halakhah, the Jewish law. Hence, Zommunity.com/Jewish would be the best place to look for or provide services and goods or even share information and help people of the same community. Rather than posting an ad on CraigsList, a Vietnamese immigrant who has just landed in LAX would prefer to find a roommate among people who speak the same language. So s/he chooses to post an ad in Zommunity.com/Vietname where the Vietnamese community in his/her city gather to buy and sell services or products or share valuable information within their community.  Zommunity is currently active in six large cities across California and Washington and is looking forward to spread all across the country.
Industry Groups: Advertising, Community and Lifestyle, Sales and Marketing
